---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Utilities · Porchlight">
  <h1>Utilities</h1>
  <p>
    A small, finite set of single-purpose helpers for accessibility, layout,
    and typography needs that recur but don't belong to a component. Porchlight
    is not utility-first: each utility earns its place by serving a recurring
    need.
  </p>

  <h2><code>.pl-u-sr-only</code> and <code>.pl-u-focusable-sr-only</code></h2>
  <p>
    Hide content from sighted users while keeping it for assistive tech. Use
    <code>.pl-u-sr-only</code> when the element should stay hidden on focus, and
    <code>.pl-u-focusable-sr-only</code> for skip links that reveal themselves.
  </p>
  <div class="demo">
    <button class="pl-c-button" data-variant="ghost" aria-label="Settings">
      ⚙ <span class="pl-u-sr-only">Settings</span>
    </button>
    <a class="pl-u-focusable-sr-only" href="#utility-focus-target">Focusable skip target</a>
    <span id="utility-focus-target" aria-hidden="true">← hidden text stays available to AT</span>
  </div>

  <h2><code>.pl-u-truncate</code></h2>
  <p>One-line truncation with an ellipsis. Use for table cells, breadcrumbs, file names.</p>
  <div class="demo">
    <div class="truncate-box">
      <span class="pl-u-truncate">a-very-long-account-name-that-should-truncate-with-an-ellipsis.webp</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2><code>.pl-u-min-0</code> and <code>.pl-u-wrap-anywhere</code></h2>
  <p>Helpers for flex/grid truncation and very long generated tokens.</p>
  <div class="demo utility-row">
    <span>Fixed label</span>
    <span class="pl-u-min-0 pl-u-truncate">a-flex-child-that-can-shrink-and-truncate-cleanly</span>
  </div>
  <div class="demo token-box">
    <code class="pl-u-wrap-anywhere">request_01JZ8Y7Q3Y1QYJH9D8A2WMV6YV_extremely_long_generated_identifier</code>
  </div>

  <h2><code>.pl-u-flow</code></h2>
  <p>Vertical rhythm for a prose block: space between children, not before/after.</p>
  <div class="demo">
    <div class="pl-u-flow">
      <p>First paragraph: no top margin.</p>
      <p>Second paragraph: spaced from the first via the sibling selector.</p>
      <p>Third paragraph: consistent rhythm throughout.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2><code>.pl-u-marginless</code></h2>
  <p>Remove default block margins from a single text element inside dense app chrome.</p>
  <div class="demo">
    <p class="pl-u-marginless">A marginless paragraph inside a compact row.</p>
  </div>

  <h2><code>.pl-u-surface</code></h2>
  <p>Panel styling for ad-hoc grouping (when you don't need a full <code>.pl-c-card</code>): bg, text, border, radius.</p>
  <div class="demo">
    <div class="pl-u-surface utility-surface">
      An ad-hoc surface: useful for inline callouts that don't deserve a component.
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2><code>.pl-u-muted</code></h2>
  <p>Secondary/caption text color.</p>
  <div class="demo">
    <p>Primary text. <span class="pl-u-muted">Secondary, muted text.</span></p>
    <p><span class="pl-u-muted-sm">Small muted metadata text.</span></p>
  </div>

  <h2><code>.pl-u-icon-title</code></h2>
  <p>Leading icon + title pattern that keeps the icon attached to the title line.</p>
  <div class="demo title-box">
    <span class="pl-u-icon-title">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h16M12 4v16" stroke-linecap="round" /></svg>
      <span class="pl-u-min-0 pl-u-truncate">Extremely long workflow title that truncates beside its icon</span>
    </span>
  </div>

  <h2>Badge/chip group</h2>
  <p>Use <code>.pl-l-cluster</code> with a smaller gap for wrapping groups of compact labels.</p>
  <div class="demo pl-l-cluster utility-chip-cluster">
    <span class="pl-c-badge">Queued</span>
    <span class="pl-c-badge" data-tone="success">Ready</span>
    <span class="pl-c-chip">Finance</span>
    <span class="pl-c-chip" data-tone="warning">Needs review</span>
  </div>

  <h2><code>.pl-u-full-bleed</code></h2>
  <p>Break an element out to the viewport edges inside a constrained container (a wide table or image in a prose column).</p>
  <div class="demo narrow">
    <div class="pl-u-surface pl-u-full-bleed utility-full-bleed">
      This breaks out beyond the narrow demo container to the viewport edges.
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .demo {
    margin-block-end: var(--pl-space-5);
  }
  .truncate-box {
    max-inline-size: 20rem;
    border: 1px dashed var(--pl-color-border);
    border-radius: var(--pl-radius-md);
    padding: var(--pl-space-2);
  }
  .truncate-box .pl-u-truncate {
    display: block;
  }
  .utility-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--pl-space-3);
    max-inline-size: 22rem;
    padding: var(--pl-space-2);
    border: 1px dashed var(--pl-color-border);
    border-radius: var(--pl-radius-md);
  }
  .token-box,
  .title-box {
    max-inline-size: 20rem;
    padding: var(--pl-space-2);
    border: 1px dashed var(--pl-color-border);
    border-radius: var(--pl-radius-md);
  }
  .pl-u-icon-title svg {
    inline-size: 1rem;
    block-size: 1rem;
  }
  .utility-surface {
    padding: var(--pl-space-4);
  }
  .utility-chip-cluster {
    --pl-l-cluster-gap: var(--pl-space-2);
  }
  .utility-full-bleed {
    padding: var(--pl-space-3);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .narrow {
    max-inline-size: 24rem;
    border-inline: 2px solid var(--pl-color-accent);
    padding: var(--pl-space-3);
  }
</style>
